message.content:
To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Mauritius, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover the 1km distance.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling is another convenient option. It will be faster than walking and also provide some exercise. You can reach the grocery store in around 5-7 minutes.

3. Public Transportation: Depending on the availability and proximity of bus stops, you can check if there is a bus route that passes near the grocery store. Public buses are a cost-effective way to travel short distances. You can inquire about the bus routes and timings from locals or at the nearest bus station.

4. Taxi or Ride-Sharing: If you prefer a more comfortable and convenient option, you can hire a taxi or use a ride-sharing service like Uber or Bolt. This will be the quickest way to reach the grocery store, taking around 3-5 minutes.

Consider the factors like weather, your preference, and availability of transportation options to choose the most suitable method for your journey.
